A Clifton bungalow has sold for R70-million. CAPE TOWN - Many of us yearn to buy our dream home but how much are we willing to spend to get it? Well, someone has parted with a cool R70-million for a Clifton bungalow. Even more astonishing is that it's only the second-highest price for a residential property on the Atlantic Seaboard this year, according to Pam Golding Properties. READ: SA lockdown: High-end property owners downscaling The highest was R75-million and if you think, the house will be occupied all-year-round, then you'd be wrong. The mega-rich buyer is using the bungalow as a holiday home.